text: there is no fracture or subluxation.vertebral body alignment is normal.the central canal appears patent at all levels, though note is made of hyperdense material within the central canal extending down to c2, consistent with extension of the intracranial extra-axial blood.there is no prevertebral soft tissue swelling.note is made of multilevel degenerative change throughout the cervical spine, with disc osteophyte complexes noted at c4/5, ___, ___, and ___.degenerative change is noted at nearly all uncovertebral joints and facet joints bilaterally.regional soft tissue structures are unremarkable.visualized portions of the lung apices are notable for apical scarring.

text: on sagittal images, the skull base to the superior portion of the t2 vertebral body are clearly visualized.equivocal prominence of the mid-inferior cervical prevertebral soft tissues appears to be related to the esophagus, which demonstrates equivocal circumferential mural thickening.there is normal alignment without fracture.mild degenerative disease of the cervical spine manifested by anterior osteophytes and disc space narrowing, most prominent at the c5/6 and c6/7 levels.there is a chronic-appearing fracture of an osteophyte emanating from the anterior-superior aspect of .there are "punched out" round lytic or cystic lesions centered in the c3 through c7 vertebral bodies.there are small disc bulges at the c3/4 and c4/5, without significant canal narrowing.scattered cervical chain lymph nodes do not meet ct criteria for pathologic enlargement.there is minimal paraseptal emphysema at the right lung apex.

text: there is no evidence of acute fracture in the cervical spine.there are severe degenerative changes seen at the levels of c3-4, c4-5, c5-6 and c6- c7.these degenerative changes include severe disc space loss, large anterior osteophytosis and disc bulges.on axial images, there is incidental note of emphysematous changes in the bilateral lung apices.there is also a large right calcified pleural plaque identified.there are multiple subcentimeter lymph nodes seen in the paratracheal and supraclavicular areas bilaterally.there is fusiform dilatation of the common carotid arteries measuring approximately 1.6 cm in longest diameter on the right and 1.4 cm in longest diameter on the left.multiple tiny hyperdense metallic foci are seen surrounding both common carotid arteries.this is of unknown etiology( ? prior surgery or xrt) and clinical correlation is recommended.there are pooled secretions seen in the posterior nasopharynx likely secondary to trauma.there is also a linear calcification identified in the right transverse foramen of the c1 process (3, 11).this may represent heavy calcification of the right vertebral artery.

text: no cortical irregularities are identified to suggest acute fracture.gross normal spinal alignment is preserved.no prevertebral soft tissue abnormality is detected.the lateral masses of c1 are well opposed on c2.the dens is intact.moderate multilevel degenerative changes are present within the cervical spine with posterior disc bulge at c3-c4, c4-c5, and c5-c6 narrowing the ventral canal mildly at these levels.at c6-c7 a moderate posterior disc bulge not well evaluated on this modality appears to impress upon the thecal sac to some degree.calcified atherosclerotic plaque at the right carotid bifurcation is moderate (series 3, image 44).subcutaneous air within the left soft tissues with tiny apical pneumothorax is noted.ill-defined opacity within the right lung apex measures 1.7 cm in a background of emphysematous change.

text: cervical spine was imaged from the level of the skull base to the inferior endplate of t2.there is no evidence of fracture or malalignment of the component vertebrae.the atlanto-occipital and atlanto-axial relationships are maintained.there is no prevertebral soft tissue swelling.there is multilevel degenerative change with loss of disc space height, osteophytes, and facet hypertrophy, most prominent at c3-4 and c4-5.slight widening of the anterior c3-4 and c4-5 disc space is likely degenerative.lobular soft tissue density in the posterior nasopharynx is incompletely characterized and may represent a nasal polyp, polypoid adenoid tissue, secretions or soft tissue mass.there is no erosion of the adjacent bony structures.there is a tiny right apical hydropneumothorax adjacent to a posterior second rib fracture.high-density material along the visualized right tentorium is consistent with known subdural hematoma.

text: there is no fracture or alignment abnormality.multilevel mild vertebral body height loss especially at c5 and c6, likely degenerative in nature.sclerotic appearance of the c5 vertebral body is noted.there are multilevel degenerative changes, especially at c5-c6 with disc desiccation and posterior disc osteophyte formation causing effacement of the anterior thecal sac.there is a large schmorl node at superior endplate of t1 vertebral body.the patient is intubated and the prevertebral soft tissues are, therefore, not well-evaluated, with mucosal edema and retained secretions.the remaining visualized soft tissues including the thyroid gland are grossly unremarkable.the lung apices demonstrate mild inter- and intralobular septal thickening which may represent a component of congestive heart failure.atelectatic versus nodular changes of the posterior left upper lobe is only partially imaged.

text: vertebral body heights are well preserved.the body alignment is notable for straightening with loss of the normal cervical lordosis; ther eis also kyphosis at c5/6 level.there is no fracture.there is no prevertebral soft tissue swelling.degenerative change is noted most prominently at c5/6 where there is loss of intervertebral disc height as well as posterior osteophyte formation which effaces the ventral thecal sac.disk osteophyte complex and uncovertebral osteophytes are noted at c5/6 level, which result in slightly widened appearance posteriorly; this is liekly related to degenerative changes rather than trauma; mr can be helpful to assess the ligaments.there is resultant mild- moderate canal stenosis and moderate-severe left neural foraminal narrowing.intracranial contents are better characterized on the separately dictated ct of the head.regional soft tissue structures of the neck are notable for atherosclerotic calcification at the coronary arteries, most notably on the left.the included portions of the lung apices reveal marked bilateral emphysematous changes.

text: since the prior study, there has been placement of new hardware along the anterolateral aspect of t12 through l2 vertebral bodies, with paired screws extending across the vertebral body of t12, and paravertebral rods extending down to the l2 level where there are another set of paired intervertebral screws.the screws are within the vertebral body without evidence of extension beyond the cortex.the previously placed posterior hardware is intact without evidence of complication.the comminuted fracture of the l1 vertebral body is again noted, and configuration of the fragments is unchanged compared to the prior study.in particular, there is no change in the position of the retropulsed fragments.if further evaluation of spinal canal decompression is indicated, an mr of the spine may be helpful.there are several foci of retroperitoneal and subcutaneous air consistent with recent post- operative state.surgical staples remainder across the skin of the lower back.the alignment of the vertebral bodies has not changed since the prior study.there is a small left- sided pleural effusion noted.there is associated lower lobe atelectasis.streak artifact from the hardware obscures adequate evaluation of the spinal canal and nerve roots at the levels where the fusion has been performed.

text: there is no evidence of fracture or abnormal alignment.mild degenerative changes are visualized with anterior osteophytes.ct is not sensitive for evaluation of intraspinal soft tissue abnormalities, but no collections or masses are identified.no osseous lesions are detected.the study is not tailored for evaluation of thoracic or abdominal structures.however, the visualized portions of these regions demonstrate dense atherosclerotic calcifications of the aortic arch with prominence of the aorta.atherosclerotic calcifications of the aortic and mitral valve annuli as well as the coronary arteries are noted in an enlarged heart.additionally, there are large bilateral pleural effusions with adjacent airspace atelectasis as well as evidence of ascites in the abdomen.there is an enlarged nodular thyroid gland, right greater than left, with multiple calcifications.
